3.1.4.3 	River
<p> You reached a crossroad in an enchanted forest. You can:

<button 1.1> Go left to shortcut in the dark part of the forest. </button>
<button 1.2> Go through the long and safe way of the forest. </button>

if (button 1.1)
    <p> You reached a one eye demon, if you want to pass this way you have to fight.
Roll the dice to see if you can bit him (demon roll dice too). </p>

playerRoll = Math.random() * 6 + 1;
demonRoll = Math.random() * 6 + 1;

while (demonRoll != playerRoll)
    playerRoll = Math.random() * 6 + 1;
    demonRoll = Math.random() * 6 + 1;

if (playerRoll > demonRoll)
    <p> You win! you can keep going through the path.

else if (demonRoll > playerRoll)
    <p> the demon wins! you lose (-10 health). To keep going you have to pay him 10$ (-10$) </p>

    if (health < 0)
	health -= 10;
        <GAME ENDS>
    if (money < 10)
	<GAME ENDS>

    money -= 10;

    // event ends

if (button 1.2):
    <p> The player keep walking and he reached a river which he have to 
cross. </p>

if (backpack contains knife or ax):
    <button 2.1> You can build a raft if you have an ax/knife. </button>
<button 2.2> Try to swim across </button>
<button 2.3> Pay the river keeper 15$ to get him across safely. </button>

    if (button 2.1):
	<p> You user your ax/knife to build a raft. you reached the other
side of the river but your tired. you lose 5 point of strength. </p>

    strength -= 5;

    if (button 2.2):
	<p> You try to swim across and you didn’t made it...
You lose 5 point of strength, And you are back on the same (-5 strength)
side of the river with the option to: </p>

<button 3.1> build a raft </button>
<button 3.2> Try to swim across </button>
if (money >= 15)
    <button 3.3> Pay the river keeper 15$ to get him across safely </button>

if (button 3.1 or button 3.2)
    <p> You made it across! </p>

    // next event

else // button 3.3
    if (money >= 40)
        money -= 40;

        <p> You payed 15$ to the river keeper. The river keeper got you across safely but stole from you $25. </p>

    else // you have less than 40 dollars
	money = 0;

	<p> You payed 15$ to the river keeper. The river keeper got you across safely but stole from you the rest of your money.

    // event ends

<<NEXT EVENT>>


