3.1.5.4 	Pyramid
// the "Along the way, you fall into a pit trap. You are lost. You continue walking around looking for an exit." story is used 3 times. Either set this event into a function or re-use it 3 times.

<p> You enter a pyramid. Curiosity got the best of you and you decided to enter the pyramid. As you walk in, the door shuts tight and you are now trapped. You notice three items floating magically above a stone. Which of these items do you pick up? </p>

// note: these items do not go into the backpack. They are temporary

<button 1.1> compass</button>
<button 1.2> flame torch</button>
<button 1.3> stack of gold</button>

temporaryItem = <<button>>

<p> You decide to pick up <<temporaryItem>>>. The other items turns into dust. You walk down the path and a mummy suddenly appears from no where. You... </p>

<button 2.1> run for your life </button>
<button 2.2> fight the mummy </button>
